      <p align="center" class="style73"><strong><a href="ESL.English.Learning.Audiobooks/ESL.English.Learning.Audiobooks.html">IT'S KIND OF A FUNNY STORY<br />
      <img src="ESL.English.Learning.Audiobooks/Kind.of.a.Funny.Story/images/150-Funny.jpg" width="150" height="150" alt="ESL & Adult Literacy Listening and Reading - Audiobooks - esl-bits.net - adult-literacy.us" /><br />
      by Ned Vizzini</a></strong></p>
      <p align="left" class="style73">&nbsp;&nbsp;Ambitious New York City teenager Craig Gilner is determined to succeed at life at any cost. But once Craig gets into an exclusive school, the pressure becomes unbearable. He stops eating and sleeping until, one night, he nearly kills himself.      After he checks into a mental hospital, he experiences a whole new world. <br />
      &nbsp;&nbsp;There are a lot of serious issues here; you can't help but read it and weep.<br />
Or laugh. Probably both.</p>
      
    <td width="16%" height="291" valign="top"><div align="center">
      <div align="center"><strong><a href="Novellas.for.ESL.Students/Novellas.for.ESL.html" class="Summary"><u>NOVELLAS</u></a><u><a href="Novellas.for.ESL.Students/Novellas.for.ESL.html"></a></u></strong>
      </div>
      
      <p align="center" class="style73"><strong><a href="Novellas.for.ESL.Students/Novellas.for.ESL.html">GOODBYE, COLUMBUS<br />

      </a></strong><a href="Novellas.for.ESL.Students/Novellas.for.ESL.html"><img src="Novellas.for.ESL.Students/Goodbye.Columbus/images/150x150-1.jpg" width="150" height="150" alt="Short Stories for English Language Learners" /><br />
      <strong>by Philip Roth</strong></a></p>
      <p align="left" class="style73"><a href="Novellas.for.ESL.Students/Novellas.for.ESL.html">Goodbye, Columbus is a coming of age story, a summer romance between a poor boy and a wealthy girl. It features Neil Klugman, a poor young man from Newark, and Brenda Patimkin, a self-assured rich girl. Neil calls Brenda for a date after first meeting her, but when she accepts and they meet, he finds that he really doesn't know what to do next. They both bumble through the beginnings of a relationship, mutually attracted physically, but diametrically opposed socially. </a>    </p>
      
    <td width="16%" height="291" valign="top"><div align="center">
